review:
This game is great (for indie puzzle), especially given that I bought it for nearly notning ($0.035).
BUT:
1) No subtitles?! Is it hard to make subtitles? It seems that the game have a deep philosophy, but Its difficult to understand by ear if english is not your best side;
2) Small bugs and unfinished details (you have to reset a level sometimes, if you are unlucky or too curious);
2.1) Bug with achievments (you cannot achieve some of them)
3) A bit disturbing (for a PUZZLE game) music, but not so bad and pretty dynamic;
4) Two or three levels, when you have to do stupid things (quick-clicking things)
All the rest are good and worth it. Puzzles are varied and interesting, but, mostly, with only one solution available and may seem too easy.
